Day 6 — Data Analysis & Preprocessing 

Date: 15-Jul-2026 

Topics Covered :

NumPy Arrays, Broadcasting, Pandas DataFrame, Reading CSV/Excel/JSON, Filtering, GroupBy, Missing Value Handling, Data Preprocessing, Feature Engineering Basics. 

Overview :

Today's focus was learning how to load, explore, clean, and prepare real-world data using NumPy and Pandas — the core toolkit for any data analysis or machine learning task. 

Key Points 

*NumPy arrays and broadcasting let us perform fast math operations on data without writing loops. 

*Pandas DataFrames store tabular data; files can be loaded directly from CSV, Excel, or JSON. 

*Filtering and groupby help extract and summarize specific parts of a dataset. 

*Missing values were handled using median (numeric) and mode (categorical) filling. 

*Preprocessing included encoding categories and scaling numeric columns for ML readiness. 

*Feature engineering created new, more useful columns like Debt-to-Income ratio and Age Group. 

*Hands-on Deliverable 

*Built and ran a complete data cleaning notebook (Day6_Data_Cleaning.ipynb) on a sample messy dataset, producing a fully cleaned and feature-engineered output file. 

Key Takeaway :

Clean, well-structured data is the foundation of good analysis — a consistent workflow (explore, clean, filter, summarize, preprocess, engineer) makes any dataset ready for real use. 